<p>I am trying to apply a certain rotation to an image, but it doesn't work as expected. The rotation I have is:</p>  <pre><code>[0.109285   0.527975    0.000000     -0.527975   0.109285    0.000000     0.000000    0.000000    1.000000] </code></pre>  <p>Which should be a rotation of ~78 degrees around the camera center (or the Z axis if you prefer). To build a homography, as there is no translation component, I use the formula: <code>K * R * K^-1</code> (infinite homography).</p>  <p>The code I use to transform the image (320x240) is:</p>  <pre><code>cv::warpPerspective(image1, image2, K * R * K.inv(), image1.size()); </code></pre>  <p>where K is:</p>  <pre><code>[276.666667 0.000000    160.000000   0.000000    276.666667  120.000000   0.000000    0.000000    1.000000] </code></pre>  <p>The resulting matrix from <code>K * R * K.inv()</code> is:</p>  <pre><code>[0.109285   0.527975    79.157461    -0.527975   0.109285    191.361865   0.000000    0.000000    1.000000] </code></pre>  <p>The result should just be a rotation of the image, but the image gets "zoomed out" like this:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/X6mcg.jpg" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/X6mcg.jpg" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>What am I doing wrong?</p>